                                    <li><a href="https://obtanicallergensaway.tk/contact/" style="font-size:16px;font-family:'Mongolian',sans-serif;padding:12px 25px;color:white">About Us</a></li>

                                </ul>
                            </nav>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!--END: NAVIGATION-->
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>

        <!-- Page title -->
        <section id="page-title"
                 style="background-image: url('../../Pictures/ChildrenMP.jpg');background-size:cover">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="page-title" style="margin-top:130px">
                    <div class="container-fluid animated fadeInDown visible" data-animate="fadeInDown" data-animate-delay="1200">
                        <p style="font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size:100px;color:orangered"> Meal Plan: Desserts</p>
                    </div>
                    <div style="margin-top:200px" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>


        <!-- end: Page title -->
        <div class="container">
            <nav class="grid-filter gf-outline" data-layout="#portfolio" style="margin-top:100px">
                <ul>
                    <li>@Html.ActionLink("Choiceness", "Index", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                    <li>@Html.ActionLink("Gluten-free", "Glutenfree", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                    <li class="active">@Html.ActionLink("Dairy-free", "Dairyfree", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                    <li>@Html.ActionLink("Peanut-free", "Peanutfree", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                    <li>@Html.ActionLink("Soy-free", "Soyfree", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                    <li>@Html.ActionLink("Tree Nut-free", "TreeNutfree", "ChildrenMP")</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="grid-active-title">Dairy-free</div>
            </nav>

            <hr />

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-9">
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                    <input type="button" class="btn btn-outline" value="Download this Plan" onclick="location.href='@Url.Action("Download","ChildrenMP",new { keyword = "Dairy" })'" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section id="page-content">
            <div class="container">
                <!-- Gallery -->
                <div class="post-3-columns">
                    <div class="post-item border">
                        <div class="post-item-wrap">
                            <div class="post-image">
                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/7465">

                                    <img src="~/Pictures/recipePics/ice cream2.png" />
                                </a>
                            </div>
                            <div class="post-item-description">
                                <h2>
                                    <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/7465">
                                        Chocolate Fudge-Almond
                                    </a>
                                </h2>
                                <p>Editor's note: The recipe and introductory text below are excerpted from Charlie Trotter and Roxanne Klein's book, Raw.</p>

                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/7465" class="item-link">Read More <i class="fa-angle-right"></i></a>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="post-item border">
                        <div class="post-item-wrap">
                            <div class="post-image">
                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/500">
                                    <img src="~/Pictures/Candy.jpg" />
                                </a>
                                <span class="post-meta-category" style="background-color:Red"><a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/500">high Rating</a></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="post-item-description">
                                <h2>
                                    <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/500">
                                        Grilled Peaches with Black Pepper and Basil-Lime Syrup
                                    </a>
                                </h2>
                                <p>
                                    The black pepper adds a surprising aromatic and spicy flavor to the sweet grilled peaches. The recipe here makes more syrup than you'll likely need but it will keep in the refrigerator for at least 1 week and is great in a cocktail or with sparkling water.
                                </p>

                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/500" class="item-link">Read More <i class="fa-angle-right"></i></a>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="post-item border">
                        <div class="post-item-wrap">
                            <div class="post-image">
                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/6865">

                                    <img src="~/Pictures/recipePics/cake1.png" />
                                </a>
                                <span class="post-meta-category" style="background-color:Red"><a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/6865">high Rating</a></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="post-item-description">
                                <h2>
                                    <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/6865">
                                        Carrot Cake with Cream Cheese-Lemon Zest Frosting
                                    </a>
                                </h2>
                                <p> It isn't too sweet, and it has a moist, dense texture from the carrots and pineapple. It's also one of my most popular cakes at weddings and parties. When I make it at home, I throw more things into the batter—for example, a handful of pumpkin seeds or toasted pecans if I have them lying around. The beauty of this recipe is that you can increase the spices or omit the nuts, and it will still taste great.</p>

                                <a href="~/ChildrenMP/Details/6865" class="item-link">Read More <i class="fa-angle-right"></i></a>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    </div>
                <!-- end: Gallery -->



            </div>
        </section>




